main event: A spherical, white metallic object was observed for one hour and forty minutes in Indian House, NWT, Canada, but disappeared when obscured by a cloud.
interesting points: The object was described as sphere-shaped, white metallic in color, and approximately the size of an aircraft at an unspecified distance.
The observation lasted for a significant duration of one hour and forty minutes.
The conclusion was inconclusive due to insufficient data for proper analysis and was categorized as possibly astronomical or unknown.
Scattered clouds and various surface weather conditions were noted during the sighting.
There was a request for the original negatives and prints of the observed object to be forwarded to a specific center, along with details about the type of camera used.
